Wave32 specialization for all MoE quant formats

## Status
Proposed

## Goal
Extend the wave32 pattern from the IQ2_XXS MoE gate/up kernel to Q2_K and Q4_K formats, replacing the generic 64-thread block kernel (~72 GiB/s ceiling per AGENTS.md).

## Context
File: ds4_rocm.c:6410, `rocm_moe_gate_up_matvec_kernel` and IQ2_XXS variant at L6531.

Current MoE gate/up matvec:
- Generic kernel (L6410): 64+ thread blocks, each thread loads x into LDS then computes its row dot. Serial inner dot over quant blocks limits throughput.
- IQ2_XXS wave variant (L6531): one 32-lane wave per output row, lanes split sub-blocks, shuffle reduction. Comment says ~2x faster.

Q2_K and Q4_K quant types still fall through to the generic kernel. They are used by many production MoE models.

## Key insight
rocm_quant_dot_block() for Q2_K/Q4_K works block-at-a-time, called sequentially per block. A wave32 variant can parallelize each block across 32 lanes using __shfl_down, similar to IQ2_XXS but with the Q2_K/Q4_K block decode logic.

